The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, December 23, 2003 				 ICICI Pru hikes capital by Rs 100 cr
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Calcutta, Dec. 22: ICICI Prudential Life Insurance has increased its capital base by Rs 100 crore, thereby increasing its total paid-up equity capital to Rs 625 crore.																								This capital infusion is the eighth equity hike since the company was incorporated in December 2000. The two partners, ICICI Bank and Prudential plc, contributed capital in their existing proportions, 74:26 respectively. The authorised capital of the firm stands at Rs 1,200 crore.																								We are confident of the long-term potential of the Indian market for life insurance and pensions, said MD Shikha Sharma.																								ICICI Prus additional equity will be primarily used to fund expansion plans. Allianz Bajaj infusion																								In the second round of equity infusion into the company, Allianz Bajaj Life Insurance Company today announced a further infusion of Rs 50 crore capital, taking the total to Rs 250 crore. Infusion of share capital is to  fuel aggressive growth plans in the near future, said Sam  Ghosh, country manager and CEO designate.
